(a bit offtopic, but...)

EP/hypoid gear oil is generally only really applicable for gearboxes with 
R&P - for some older gearboxes with detached R&P the transmission itself 
is usually filled with straight mineral oil (often subsituted today w/ 
motor oil).  FWIW.  There really are cases where engine oil in the gearbox 
is the right thing.



